text.section:
The policy summary required to be delivered under subsection (a) of this section shall include:
information required to be included in an outline of coverage under § 18-106 of this title;
an explanation of how the long-term care benefits interact with other components of the life insurance policy, including deductions from death benefits;
an illustration of the amount of benefits, length of benefit, and guaranteed lifetime benefits if any, for each covered individual;
any exclusions, reductions, or limitations on benefits of long-term care; and
if applicable to the policy type:
a disclosure of the effects of exercising other rights under the policy;
a disclosure of guarantees related to long-term care costs of insurance charges; and
current and projected maximum lifetime benefits.
